{\textbf{Problem}: Traditional automotive body control systems face challenges in integrating various subsystems efficiently, leading to increased wiring complexity and communication delays.\\
\vspace{1pt}
\textbf{Implemented}: Designed a body control module using the CAN protocol to integrate and manage automotive subsystems like lighting, wipers, and door locks. Ensured efficient communication and reduced wiring complexity through CAN-based messaging.\\

\vspace{1pt}
\textbf{Key Skills}: Embedded Systems, CAN Protocol, Automotive Electronics, Microcontrollers, C Programming.}\\
